      <h2>🎓 Vision</h2>
      <p>To train passionate, Spirit-filled men and women to plant churches, disciple communities, and serve the body of Christ with sound doctrine and practical skills.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="mission">
      <h2>🧭 Mission</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Equip students with strong biblical and theological foundations</li>
        <li>Prepare church planters to engage in real urban ministry</li>
        <li>Offer practical and livelihood electives to support full-time ministry</li>
        <li>Disciple servant leaders for long-term local and global mission</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section id="programs">
      <h2>🏫 Program Highlights</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Trimester System (3 terms per year)</li>
        <li>3-Year Classroom Learning + 4th Year Internship</li>
        <li>10 Units per Trimester only (manageable load)</li>
        <li>4 Levels of Church Planting Courses</li>
        <li>Focus on Urban Evangelism & Ministry</li>
        <li>Livelihood-Based Electives for Tentmaking Pastors</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>📚 Academic Programs Offered</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Certificate in Church Planting</strong> – 12 Units</li>
        <li><strong>Diploma in Theology</strong> – 2 Years</li>
        <li><strong>Bachelor of Theology (Ecclesiastical)</strong> – 4 Years
          <ul>
            <li>Pastoral Studies Track</li>
            <li>Christian Education for Ladies</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>
    <section id="faculty">
      <h2>🧑‍🏫 Faculty</h2>
      <p>Our instructors are seasoned CAMACOP pastors and educators with <strong>Master’s and Doctorate degrees</strong>, trained in both academic excellence and practical ministry.</p>
